/*!

\page rmol-config
	Configuration Script for the C++ Revenue Management Optimisation Library

\section sec_synopsis SYNOPSIS
<b>rmol-config</b> <tt>[--prefix] [--version] [--libs] [--cflags]</tt>

\section sec_description DESCRIPTION

\e rmol-config is a tool that is used by configure to determine the
compiler and linker flags that should be used to compile and link
programs that use \e RMOL. It is also used internally by the .m4
macros, that are included with \e RMOL, for GNU autoconf.

\section sec_options OPTIONS

\e rmol-config accepts the following options:

 \b --version<br>
    Print the currently installed version of RMOL on the standard output.

 \b --sampledir<br>
    Show where the (CSV) sample files are located.

 \b --libs<br>
    Print the linker flags that are necessary to link with the RMOL library.

 \b --cflags<br>
    Print the compiler flags that are necessary to compile with the
    RMOL library.

 \b --prefix<br>
    Show the RMOL installation prefix.

\section sec_see_also SEE ALSO
 \b rmol(1), \b rmol-config(1), \b boost-config(1)

